WEBVTT

00:00.162 --> 00:03.426
Grace, mercy, and peace be unto you from our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.

00:04.407 --> 00:06.890
And again, a portion of the gospel reading this evening.

00:07.471 --> 00:11.796
He came to her and said, greetings, O favorite one, the Lord is with you.

00:13.338 --> 00:17.984
But she was greatly troubled at the saying and tried to discern what sort of greeting this might be.

00:18.024 --> 00:24.171
And the angel said to her, do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favor with God.

00:25.113 --> 00:26.114
If you join me with a word of prayer.

00:27.616 --> 00:29.618
Lord God, as we gather before you this evening,

00:29.890 --> 00:33.855
as we draw closer to the celebration of your son's birth.

00:34.316 --> 00:42.507
We give thanks for this season, the reminder to wait and to look and to watch, and also to know who this one who is coming is.

00:42.567 --> 00:45.371
This Jesus, your own son, come into the world.

00:45.811 --> 00:59.730
Tonight we see him as the true king, the one who follows in the lineage of David, but one who is the greater David, the one who can truly sit on the king and rule with justice and righteous and holiness for his people.

01:00.034 --> 01:12.993
So lower, we ask that those gifts, those characteristics would come into our lives also, that your justice would fill us, your holiness would be with us, and that you would lead us on paths of mercy as we go through this world.

01:13.434 --> 01:14.796
We pray all this now in Jesus' name.

01:15.617 --> 01:15.858
Amen.

01:16.899 --> 01:17.701
Congregation, may be seated.

01:17.741 --> 01:29.298
The season of Advent is always a bit tricky to preach through and to plan sermons for, because

01:29.762 --> 01:33.948
the well-known passages that we come across during the season are so well-known.

01:35.030 --> 01:55.120
The story is so well-known and so often told, and so we go through the season always thinking about it at the beginning of Advent, what are the sermons going to be like, what are our Sundays going to be like, what are our Wednesdays going to be like, and especially as we think about Christmas Eve, which is a unique service because we have a lot of people who join us who aren't here every Sunday.

01:55.140 --> 01:59.186
A lot of families are gathered together, people of all ages, including many

01:59.394 --> 02:00.936
Many kids are here with us that evening.

02:00.976 --> 02:06.161
And so some things that might work other times don't work for Christmas Eve, that large service.

02:07.002 --> 02:12.609
And generally, we know people want to come and they want to hear a joyful telling of the Christmas story.

02:12.689 --> 02:21.258
So doing things like a deep dive into the Greek grammar might not work on Christmas Eve, but maybe it could work tonight.

02:23.901 --> 02:28.306
If we do slow down and take a look at this passage from Luke chapter one,

02:28.418 --> 02:37.349
Of course, we know it, but there's a lot here that is still worth reflecting on, really slowing down and honing in on.

02:37.409 --> 02:53.289
And what I believe we find here when we do that is that Luke chapter one, especially these verses of the angel coming to Mary, pronounce the good news that a Savior is going to be born, that she would give birth to a son.

02:53.309 --> 02:57.234
In many, many ways, this is a reversal

02:57.890 --> 03:00.913
of the curse that comes to mankind in Genesis chapter three.

03:02.474 --> 03:06.839
Might not seem like it at first, but we'll see if we can put that together in the next few minutes.

03:08.560 --> 03:11.363
So Luke one here, the angel comes to the Lord.

03:11.383 --> 03:13.765
That's where this portion of the story begins.

03:13.785 --> 03:18.970
The angel comes from God himself and invites Mary to come close.

03:20.011 --> 03:21.533
So God is coming close to Mary.

03:21.553 --> 03:27.218
Mary is coming close to God by this messenger, this angelic being who now comes to Mary.

03:28.226 --> 03:34.457
He's bringing a message of good news, though she doesn't understand it at first, and though she has questions, she wants to know how these things will be.

03:34.497 --> 03:36.080
It is a message of good news.

03:36.140 --> 03:39.305
God is coming down in a new way.

03:39.846 --> 03:45.115
He is drawing near to his people and first to marry herself.

03:46.918 --> 03:51.346
If you go all the way back to Genesis chapter three, you have the fall,

03:52.482 --> 03:54.244
You have the temptation of Adam and Eve.

03:54.304 --> 04:01.534
You have the curses that are given because of the sin that they entered into, because they ate the fruit of the tree that God had commanded them not to eat.

04:01.874 --> 04:11.507
And at the very end of that chapter, they are removed from the garden of Eden, chased out, and who is there guarding the gate?

04:12.568 --> 04:14.130
What says there's a cherubim

04:14.626 --> 04:15.527
and a flaming sword.

04:15.567 --> 04:19.754
So there you have guarding the gates to Eden, to paradise and to the very presence of God.

04:20.094 --> 04:26.564
You have a messenger of God, an angelic being of God, a cherubim who's there guarding the way.

04:27.125 --> 04:36.820
You can't come in in your sinfulness and your fallenness as human people no longer permitted to enter into Eden, chased out, removed from the presence of God.

04:38.342 --> 04:43.570
But here in Luke chapter one, now the angel's coming to Mary.

04:43.970 --> 04:47.995
Now God is coming close, and God is inviting Mary to come close to Him.

04:48.056 --> 04:55.686
So we see here at the beginning that this story is starting to unfold and the things that began to happen there at the time of the fall.

04:55.966 --> 04:58.710
Genesis chapter three, maybe there is hope.

05:00.012 --> 05:04.458
Maybe God's people can be invited back in again, maybe possibly somehow.

05:05.760 --> 05:08.383
God and His people may dwell together once again.

05:08.423 --> 05:13.330
The angel comes, Gabriel comes to a virgin betrothed to a man.

05:15.330 --> 05:18.515
And this is significant as well.

05:18.595 --> 05:34.418
A young woman, a virgin as it had been promised by the prophets, but also in every possible way, the last person that anyone would expect that God's promise of salvation would come to and come through.

05:34.882 --> 05:38.366
In many ways, she's the wrong one because that's what the world would say.

05:38.406 --> 05:49.780
They look at her and especially now a virgin, a young woman, a very young woman who's not yet married and she's going to become pregnant and have to carry a child and how are others going to look at her and what are they going to think about her and what will they say about her?

05:51.802 --> 05:53.525
And yet this is the one that God chooses.

05:55.006 --> 05:55.887
She's the wrong gender.

05:56.408 --> 05:59.552
Women were not looked highly upon at that time.

06:00.072 --> 06:04.658
She's the wrong age, not old enough, even hardly old enough to be married, let alone

06:04.898 --> 06:05.519
have a child.

06:05.759 --> 06:07.300
She's from the wrong family background.

06:08.221 --> 06:12.265
She's from a small out of the way place, going to Bethlehem, a small out of the way place.

06:12.625 --> 06:15.668
She's not anybody that anybody would make much of.

06:17.090 --> 06:22.975
And significantly, she's the wrong marital status for having a child.

06:25.118 --> 06:33.906
But again, remember back to Genesis chapter 3, the part of the curse that is spoken to the woman that you will have pain in childbirth.

06:34.626 --> 06:47.584
and difficulty, a curse that is put upon humankind because the very act of bringing additional human people into the world of bearing children is going to be difficult and challenging and fraught.

06:48.926 --> 06:51.971
And sometimes it will come with sadness as well.

06:53.753 --> 06:59.882
But now in that very gift, the very thing that was once cursed, now a promise is given.

06:59.942 --> 07:02.706
Now good news is coming.

07:02.978 --> 07:07.623
Now a reversal is being made possible that the very act of childbearing.

07:08.924 --> 07:11.246
Now this will bring good news to the world.

07:11.306 --> 07:13.949
This will bring God's plan of salvation to his people.

07:14.409 --> 07:19.935
So even there that curse that was once given is now becoming a promise.

07:21.456 --> 07:25.380
The angel came to a young woman and told her that she would give birth to a son.

07:25.440 --> 07:31.026
And not only that, but that she is highly favored.

07:31.906 --> 07:35.832
One of the Greek words in there, it's a bit of a lengthy one.

07:35.892 --> 07:45.769
The translation that we have of it in English is you who are highly favored or more literal translation, you who are favored with grace.

07:47.552 --> 07:48.994
Keker Ito Mini.

07:49.635 --> 07:52.379
Keker Ito Mini is the Greek.

07:52.399 --> 07:53.722
You who are favored with grace.

07:55.484 --> 07:56.466
But how can that be?

07:57.122 --> 08:09.357
Isn't Mary like all other human people, one of the curse, one who is sinful, one who necessarily is far from God, one who cannot be given salvation even?

08:10.979 --> 08:18.067
Because she like every other human person is plagued with sin and pride and selfishness and being made far from God.

08:19.309 --> 08:26.738
And yet this is the greeting of the angel, you who are favored with grace.

08:28.546 --> 08:29.728
And she's just the first one.

08:31.690 --> 08:36.377
Because of Mary and because this gift is given to her, this will be now the promise for all of God's people.

08:36.757 --> 08:46.871
You who are favored with grace, this is what the angels say as they come and they proclaim the good news from the heavens, God's peace to all people on whom his favor rests.

08:48.693 --> 08:50.055
All people are now being favored.

08:50.456 --> 08:58.226
Those who are once cursed, who are once far from God, who are once lost in sin, now again, favored with grace.

08:59.682 --> 09:18.426
And only because of one thing, this gift that is given, a son is being born, a child is coming into the world who will be one who is going to bring some new pathway to knowing God and resting in God's presence and living in a new peace that only he makes possible.

09:20.589 --> 09:27.858
And for me, the most significant word of all of this in chapter, in verse 35, if you want to take a look at it, you can.

09:29.698 --> 09:35.465
We have the promise that's being given here is that the holy one of God is now being born of a woman.

09:35.506 --> 09:36.987
This is what the angel says.

09:37.027 --> 09:40.232
The holy one is who you're going to give birth to.

09:40.252 --> 09:42.615
The holy one of God is now coming to you.

09:42.635 --> 09:44.397
He will be called holy, the holy one.

09:44.437 --> 09:50.325
But in that verse, the word that's used is Haggion.

09:50.365 --> 09:52.347
And that word means holy.

09:52.648 --> 09:53.789
And it doesn't say holy one.

09:53.809 --> 09:57.554
A literal translation would be just the holy.

09:58.658 --> 10:02.181
The holy of God is going to be born.

10:02.201 --> 10:07.967
We were just talking in the Tuesday class this week about God's holiness.

10:08.027 --> 10:13.692
And every time you encounter God's holiness in the Old Testament, it's sort of this thing for the people in the Old Testament, God's people.

10:14.573 --> 10:15.854
They can't live without it.

10:16.014 --> 10:20.418
They long for the holiness and the presence of God, but they also really can't live with it.

10:21.700 --> 10:28.466
Because for sinful people, people who are fallen, people who are not holy, people who are finite, who are far from God,

10:29.922 --> 10:31.023
Holiness is dangerous.

10:32.705 --> 10:34.808
Holiness is problematic.

10:34.828 --> 10:38.713
It's sort of like the radiance and the power and the warmth of the sun.

10:39.093 --> 10:42.017
It is too much for human beings to bear or to handle.

10:42.057 --> 10:47.183
And so in the Old Testament, whenever someone gets a little too close to the holiness of God, they are struck down.

10:47.203 --> 10:48.565
It can cause damage to them.

10:48.605 --> 10:50.627
It can end their lives in a moment.

10:52.870 --> 10:59.218
And yet what the angel says to Mary is that being born to you is the holy

11:00.258 --> 11:03.061
of God, the holiness of God.

11:03.661 --> 11:10.348
The holiness of God is coming now to dwell in a woman is going to dwell within her in a very physical and literal sense.

11:11.930 --> 11:13.211
And he will be called the son of God.

11:14.072 --> 11:24.942
The holiness of God is now coming down is breaking through the barrier between heaven and earth is now going to be coming into a woman to dwell within her first, but then to be given to the world in childbirth.

11:26.564 --> 11:28.626
This is Jesus Christ our Lord.

11:29.474 --> 11:35.002
We praise and who we come to know during this season, the very Son of God being born into creation.

11:37.726 --> 11:42.413
And finally, to not forget about Joseph, the man.

11:42.934 --> 11:45.718
Much of this is about Mary and this gift, this promise that's given to her.

11:45.778 --> 11:50.886
She is favored and chosen for this most important of works and jobs.

11:51.066 --> 11:53.509
And she has lifted up high because of all of this.

11:54.691 --> 11:59.378
But Joseph here is mentioned as well, verse 27, to a verge of betrothed to a man whose name was Joseph.

11:59.842 --> 12:01.664
of the house of David.

12:02.184 --> 12:12.114
Get the little inkling there that he does come from a royal house, and yet it's almost as if that royalty has been forgotten, Joseph, now far from David, far removed.

12:14.417 --> 12:25.488
The one thing, and you remember the curse that's given to mankind, to men, to man, at the time of the fall, is that your work will be difficult.

12:26.549 --> 12:27.730
Tending the ground will

12:28.066 --> 12:28.907
grow up weeds.

12:29.268 --> 12:31.210
You will struggle in the work that you do.

12:31.671 --> 12:39.041
It's always been the case and one of the work that man has tried to do through the Old Testament is to draw close to God, to be close to God, to live up to God's commands.

12:39.401 --> 12:45.750
It's the work of attempting to be holy like God and yet never able, never being able to do it.

12:47.552 --> 12:54.802
But now here comes a new man going to live into that curse also so that even though our work

12:55.138 --> 12:56.019
cannot save us.

12:56.099 --> 13:03.449
Here is one who is coming whose work will save us, redeeming even the curse of work that is pronounced upon Adam.

13:04.551 --> 13:12.442
Now Jesus in his work, in the things that he does, in his accomplishments, in his doing, in his going to the cross, and in his resurrection from the dead.

13:14.204 --> 13:20.272
He brings about salvation for all mankind, all those who call on the name of the Lord.

13:21.754 --> 13:24.338
So in so many ways here, for Mary,

13:25.154 --> 13:50.546
for Joseph, for humankind, for childbirth, for the curse of work that has given in all of these ways, God is reversing the curse that was once spoken over humankind in the garden, the curse that chased them out of Eden, out of the perfect dwelling place of God, out of the place where they were made to live, and now by the grace of God and the work of Jesus Christ, now they are being brought back in, we are being invited back.

13:51.458 --> 13:55.485
brought close to God through no work of our own, but by His work only.

13:56.907 --> 14:00.593
And this is the gift that we celebrate in this season.

14:01.956 --> 14:17.522
God and His love has seen fit to come down and to be with us, to be born of a virgin, to come into this world and walk with us, to show us His mercy, His grace, His comfort, to heal the sick, to raise up the lowly, and most of all,

14:18.082 --> 14:20.908
who allow us to dwell in the presence of God once again.

14:20.968 --> 14:26.080
He is the true king, the one worthy of our praise and our worship.

14:27.102 --> 14:32.334
So I pray this season we see him, we receive him, and we praise him.

14:33.917 --> 14:34.258
Amen.

